The paper focuses on analyzing code reuse and vulnerabilities in the Ethereum smart contract ecosystem, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the similarity of contracts, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The large-scale analysis of the ecosystem involves data processing and analysis, which falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves detecting plagiarized DApps, which falls under the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
